			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not much actual change is likely to take place, but i want to keep hitting the major issues. probably bullet statement form. so here is what i am thinking now....
<br />

<br />
%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#
<br />
This report will just cover the most basic and broken issues with the class. Not all issues will be covered, and not too much detail will be presented, as almost all of them are old hat anyway.
<br />

<br />
A) PETS
<br />

<br />
The pets are still debuffed horribly upon charming. We do NOT have equal con pets after charming them, and test after test has verified this. Still no response or word if it is intended that a level 50 MOB chamred will fight as a level 46 or so.
<br />

<br />
There are new areas in the game where we no longer have access to pets also. Please don't just toss some Boogeys in there like in the catacombs... we need a real solution. Maybe allow us to charm undead finally. We have been fighting necromancy, WITH necromancy, for ever. Most of the known Sorcerors of the realm are known to use and know the secrets of necromancy. and NOW we have to be allies with necromancers. So let us charm undead and call it done. most of the areas we have pet problems are rife with undead, so this would solve it.
<br />

<br />
Maybe we shoudl just finally be able to charm anything that isn't named. We are the masters of charming pets and controlling minds, right?
<br />

<br />
And we are still the only pet reliant class to not gain Minion Control as an RA. we have the hgihest XP drain (max 50%), and no chance to reduce that amount. The RAs were not supposed to have heavy PvE impact, but this one certainly does. It is by nature a PvE only ability. And it is one that would directly help us as pet casters, but we can't gain access to it.
<br />

<br />
Why must we be forced to seek a pet.... charm it and have it reduced in level effectiveness.... and STILL expend 505 XP to it while hunting?
<br />

<br />
B) RVR
<br />

<br />
Ok, we are very reliant on our pet, in both PvE and RvR. In PvE we can hunt in areas where we can acquire new pets, so this can minimize things, but it does limit where we may freely hunt. we can spec body and Matter, relying less (or not at all) on a pet, but then we sacrifice the CC capabilities that Albion is sorely lacking. so what can we do? How can we be more effective overall, and less reliant on the pet?
<br />

<br />
First, the pet is all we really have to harm keep doors. In this stage of RvR, we really do suffer. Yet, acid eats through wood. why does our DOT not effect wooden doors? Can we have the DOT effect doors? This would not be over-powered, as they can only stack so much. 
<br />

<br />
Single target mez breaker is useful for one thing, and on thing alone. Once i mez a target, and charm them as a pet, it then prevents me from having to wait the full mez duration for my pet. it has almost no practical use in rvR due to it's limited nature. make it act as purge? Sure... clear nearsight? SOMETHING should be able to.... be AE? Maybe. but right now, it does not really help the effort much.
<br />

<br />
We have no AE attacks. We arre one of very few casters without the ability to generate AE damage, and that IS what RvR is starting to rely on more. AE DOT or AE DD, something. Or, make debuffs flag as damage for RP splits... then at least they woudl be worth casting once. But as it stands, much of what we do has no effect in RvR, it is limited in RvR, or it gains no RPs in RvR.
<br />

<br />
The fact that we can not match the oher realms due to instants is apparently a moot point, with no changes forthcoming. we don't WANT an instant, hell... most woudl love to see less instants or even none in the game. But if instants ARe in game, and they remain on par with the full cast versions of the CC spells, the Sorceror (and Albion) will forever be outclasses in this department.
<br />

<br />
C) OVERALL
<br />

<br />
We do no have much group welcome. There are some groups where CC is needed, bu that does not mean a Sorc is needed. There is rarely a time where our CC is needed for it's extra power, and we offer nothing else to a group that the other CC capable class can not do better.
<br />

<br />
The AF boost of our level 49 spell, which everyon else gets at level 50, still puts us slightly lower and has not been fixed (as far as I ecall).
<br />

<br />
Interruptions are atrocious still, and no progress seems to be made to rectify this. Some testing seems to indicate the weapon speed of the weapon you weild dictates your recast timer. If this is the case, can we have focus items with a lower delay added? how about ceremonial daggers at Del 2 sec, or focus wands with a Del of 1 sec? As it stands now, our only option is to go with nothing in our hands, which means we waste power since the game requires a focus staff for effectiveness.
<br />

<br />
%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#%#
<br />

<br />
So this is what i am thinking of posting, let me know if you think i missed anything off major importance. understand, we arekinda in a holding pattern, but i want to keep the attention on outstanding issues we have dealt with for far too long.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
