				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Maybe reverse psychology will work
<br />

<br />
1. <span style="font-weight: bold">Pets</span> are too powerful, I can easily solo several gray and green con opponents with just my pet and me. At times I've even taken down multiple blues using this tactic.
<br />

<br />
2. <span style="font-weight: bold">Mesmerize</span> is still extremely overpowered in RvR. I strongly suggest you increase resists increase casting duration.
<br />

<br />
3. <span style="font-weight: bold">Debuffs</span>, I hear some Sorcerers are actually using these now. This obviously proves they have some effectiveness. Which should be eliminated immediately.
<br />

<br />
4. <span style="font-weight: bold">Interruptions</span>, I think we will all agree here. Sharp and or shiny objects should always distract a spell cast.
<br />

<br />
5. <span style="font-weight: bold">Speed Buff</span>, Its completely unfair that a caster wearing fabric clothing can out run a fully armored warrior carrying multiple weapons. I think if we point our sharp weapons at a caster it should immobilize them.
<br />

<br />
I hope with these steps we can create a more balanced environment that all classes can enjoy.
<br />

<br />
Thank you,
<br />
Garen, Sorcerer Primas of Percival</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
