			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A) PETS
<br />
I don't think it's neccesary to go off on a tangent about your take on Necromancy. Just raise the point that we don't get pets in lots of places (a list of zones with few or no pets too), and suggest that the right answer would be to broaden our charming abilities rather than dump in a few animals 1 yr after a zone is open (catacombs).
<br />

<br />
As far as pet debuffing, if we're unintentionally affected by game code, then we should be granted a few pet-only buffs in our Mind line. Probably true of other pet charming classes. If it's there expressly to lower the effectiveness of charmed pets, then they need to re-examine that rationale. As it stands, summoned pets are absurdly easy to come by in comparison to charmed pets, and the caster can buff them to a point where they'd beat the crap out of any charmed pet (from a same lvl sorc).
<br />

<br />
Why must charm have a short range? The only purpose it serves is to occasionally get the caster killed during charming. Which turns people off from using pets.
<br />

<br />
B) RVR
<br />
I strongly suggest putting in the thing about body resists. We are the only cloth caster that has a the baseline/spec nukes on a body resist. Also, CD  seems to benefit from a matter spec - kind of uniquely gimped as far as RA's go. I like your suggestion about interruptions, but also Jenlei's point about slower weapons needing some kind of penalty in ability to interrupt is a good one.
<br />

<br />
Having pets keep agro on targets after the death of the sorceror would also help the viability of charmed pets in rvr. This is another example where Mythic nerfed something and never looked back. It is unfair and illogical that the only tactic needed to kill a charmed pet caster is mezz the pet (if it's particularly nasty) and kill the squishy pet caster.
<br />

<br />
C) OVERALL
<br />
Nice point about not being needed in groups. Might want to raise the whole pygmy issue at that point. It was the first and last prime hunting spot where sorcs were sought out, and now it's just another spot. No comment as to whether it needed nerfing or not, but it's less popular now and we're still not welcome elsewhere.
<br />

<br />
I still would love to hear any Mythic comment on why the pve resist rates for sorc mezzes are so much worse than our roots. And why mezz resist rates are worse than for minstrels. I think it has to do with resist codes for cloth casters being nerfed. Of course, the Mythic comment to this would be 'huh?' because they have no clue what is going on there, same as with every other unintentional nerf to our class.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
